==English==

===Etymology===

From {{inh|en|enm|step-}}, from {{inh|en|ang|stēop-||deprived of a relative, step-|pos=prefix}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*steupa-||orphaned, step-}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*(s)tewp-||to push, strike}}.

Cognate with {{cog|sco|step-||step-}}, {{cog|fy|stiep-||step-}}, {{cog|nl|stief-||step-}}, {{cog|nds|steef-||step-}}, {{cog|de|stief-||step-}}, {{cog|sv|styv-||step-}}, {{cog|is|stjúp-||step-}}.  Related to {{cog|ang|stīepan||to deprive, bereave}}.  Not, however, related to the familiar English noun or verb {{m|en|step}}.

===Prefix===
{{en-prefix}}

# A prefix used before ''father'', ''mother'', ''brother'', ''sister'', ''son'', ''daughter'', ''child'', and so forth, to indicate that the person being identified is not a [[blood relative]] but is related through the [[marriage]] of a parent.

